.TH "BLUETOOTHCTL-TELEPHONY" "1" "May 2025" "BlueZ" "Linux System Administration"
.SH NAME
bluetoothctl-telephony \- Telephony Submenu
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sp
\fBbluetoothctl\fP [\-\-options] [telephony.commands]
.sp
This submenu manages telephony features using the \fBorg.bluez.Telephony(5)\fP
and \fBorg.bluez.Call(5)\fP interfaces.
.SH TELEPHONY COMMANDS
.SS list
.sp
List available audio gateways.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> list\fP
.TP
.B Example Display all available HFP audio gateways
.nf
\fB> list\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS show
.sp
Show audio gateway information.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> show [telephony]\fP
.TP
.B Uses
\fBorg.bluez.Telephony(5)\fP properties
.TP
.B [telephony]
Audio gateway device path (optional, shows current if omitted)
.TP
.B Example Show information for currently selected audio gateway
.nf
\fB> show\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Show information for specific audio gateway device
.nf
\fB> show /org/bluez/hci0/dev_00_11_22_33_44_55\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Show information for another audio gateway
.nf
\fB> show /org/bluez/hci0/dev_AA_BB_CC_DD_EE_FF\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS select
.sp
Select default audio gateway.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> select <telephony>\fP
.TP
.B <telephony>
Audio gateway device path to set as default
.TP
.B Example Select specific audio gateway as default
.nf
\fB> select /org/bluez/hci0/dev_00_11_22_33_44_55\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Select different audio gateway as default
.nf
\fB> select /org/bluez/hci0/dev_AA_BB_CC_DD_EE_FF\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS dial
.sp
Dial number.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> dial <number> [telephony]\fP
.TP
.B Uses
\fBorg.bluez.Telephony(5)\fP method \fBDial\fP
.TP
.B <number>
Phone number to dial
.TP
.B [telephony]
Audio gateway device path (optional, uses current if omitted)
.TP
.B Example Dial number using currently selected audio gateway
.nf
\fB> dial 555\-1234\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Dial international number using current audio gateway
.nf
\fB> dial +1\-555\-123\-4567\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Dial emergency number using current audio gateway
.nf
\fB> dial 911\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Dial number using specific audio gateway
.nf
\fB> dial 555\-1234 /org/bluez/hci0/dev_00_11_22_33_44_55\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Dial UK number using specific audio gateway
.nf
\fB> dial +44\-20\-7946\-0958 /org/bluez/hci0/dev_AA_BB_CC_DD_EE_FF\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Dial with caller ID blocking
.nf
\fB> dial *67\-555\-1234\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Dial with caller ID hiding (GSM format)
.nf
\fB> dial #31#555\-1234\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS hangup\-all
.sp
Hangup all calls.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> hangup\-all [telephony]\fP
.TP
.B Uses
\fBorg.bluez.Telephony(5)\fP method \fBHangupAll\fP
.TP
.B [telephony]
Audio gateway device path (optional, uses current if omitted)
.TP
.B Example Terminate all active and waiting calls on current gateway
.nf
\fB> hangup\-all\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Terminate all calls on specific audio gateway
.nf
\fB> hangup\-all /org/bluez/hci0/dev_00_11_22_33_44_55\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS list\-calls
.sp
List available calls.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> list\-calls\fP
.TP
.B Example Display all active, waiting, and held calls
.nf
\fB> list\-calls\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS show\-call
.sp
Show call information.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> show\-call <call>\fP
.TP
.B Uses
\fBorg.bluez.Call(5)\fP properties
.TP
.B <call>
Call object path to display information for
.TP
.B Example Show information for specific call
.nf
\fB> show\-call /org/bluez/hci0/dev_00_11_22_33_44_55/call1\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Show information for another call
.nf
\fB> show\-call /org/bluez/hci0/dev_00_11_22_33_44_55/call2\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Show call information from different device
.nf
\fB> show\-call /org/bluez/hci0/dev_AA_BB_CC_DD_EE_FF/call1\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS answer
.sp
Answer call.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> answer <call>\fP
.TP
.B Uses
\fBorg.bluez.Call(5)\fP method \fBAnswer\fP
.TP
.B <call>
Call object path to answer
.TP
.B Example Answer incoming call
.nf
\fB> answer /org/bluez/hci0/dev_00_11_22_33_44_55/call1\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Answer waiting call
.nf
\fB> answer /org/bluez/hci0/dev_00_11_22_33_44_55/call2\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Answer call from different device
.nf
\fB> answer /org/bluez/hci0/dev_AA_BB_CC_DD_EE_FF/call1\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
.SS hangup
.sp
Hangup call.
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> hangup <call>\fP
.TP
.B Uses
\fBorg.bluez.Call(5)\fP method \fBHangup\fP
.TP
.B <call>
Call object path to terminate
.TP
.B Example Terminate specific active call
.nf
\fB> hangup /org/bluez/hci0/dev_00_11_22_33_44_55/call1\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Terminate waiting or held call
.nf
\fB> hangup /org/bluez/hci0/dev_00_11_22_33_44_55/call2\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Terminate call from different device
.nf
\fB> hangup /org/bluez/hci0/dev_AA_BB_CC_DD_EE_FF/call1\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
